GBR35,48, a flexible non-parametric statistical machine leaning algorithm in the open-source scikit-learn package49, is implemented to predict bandgaps of undiscovered HOIPs. The learning principle of this method is to improve the accuracy of the final regression results by gradually reducing the algorithm generated by the training process. The final regression algorithm is the weighted sum of several weak regression algorithms obtained by each training, as1FMx= ∑m=1MTx,θm,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
